Anograde Ranking

Anograde Physical Form ranking

The Anograde ranking system is a classification system used to measure how force-evolved a creature is. All creatures begin at a baseline ranking of A (natural form), and may shift along the scale based on factors like realm influence, magic material exposure, or external anatomical growth during gestation or post-birth transformation.

The scale serves as a metric for understanding the Post-evolution of species, particularly in realms where physical form can be altered by magic or environmental conditions.

Scale rankings:

A – Natural feral shape, often quadrupedal, natural proportions and posture.
B – feral shape with slightly softened features or expressive anatomy.
C – Primarily feral body, but hints of humanoid limb flexibility or expressiveness.
D – Quadrupedal, but can stand or sit upright briefly, limb proportions start to vary.
E – Transitional build; forelimbs resemble arms more than legs, occasional upright movement.
F – Frequently upright, digitigrade stance, arms clearly separated from front legs.
G – Fully bipedal, but retains overall feral proportions in torso and head.
H – Upright posture with more defined shoulders, chest, and hips; feral head remains.
I – Mostly humanoid build with clearly feral head, tail, and limb shapes.
J – Humanlike body structure with stylized animal features (e.g. snout, paws, ears).
K – Human body with minimal animal traits like tail, ears, light fur, or non-human eyes.
